videos.description: P.J. Thompson nails the triple after Purdue pulls down two offensive rebounds on the same possession.
videos.headline: Purdue's Thompson drains three

videos.description: Jake Ohmer gets trapped after picking up his dribble but drains the jumper anyway.
videos.headline: Western Kentucky's Ohmer hits tough shot

videos.description: Western Kentucky's Marek Nelson gets in the Thanksgiving spirit with a big block.
videos.headline: Nelson provides the stuffing

videos.description: Jake Ohmer drills a triple to give Western Kentucky a 42-31 lead at halftime against No. 18 Purdue.
videos.headline: Ohmer hits 3 before half

videos.description: Dwight Coleby gets offensive rebound and dunks the putback with emphasis.
videos.headline: Western Kentucky's Coleby throws it down

videos.description: Western Kentucky's Dariius Thompson throws a no look pass to Justin Johnson for the slam.
videos.headline: Thompson hits Johnson for alley-oop

videos.description: Vincent Edwards puts together a couple of nice post moves and cuts the Boilermaker deficit to 4.
videos.headline: Purdue's Edwards works the post

videos.description: Justin Johnson makes a nice move and lays it in to give Western Kentucky a 5-point lead late in the game.
videos.headline: Western Kentucky's Johnson makes clutch layup
